    "narrative": "Our offensive engine today is anchored by **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who commands an elite score of 81.07. Facing Corbin, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** benefits from a rare intersection of a favorable park, moderate SP skill, and a \"Slow SP Delivery\" factor that bolsters his stolen base potential\u2014a critical component for LawDog\u2019s roster construction. Following him is **Daulton Varsho**, our highest-rated outfielder at 70.35. **Daulton Varsho** is a prime start against Cecconi, with a dual boost from park dimensions and the pitcher's high stolen base concession rate, maximizing his utility in a category where we prioritize speed. Meanwhile, **Cal Raleigh** (65.16) and **Jonathan Aranda** (64.73) provide robust secondary scoring, with **Jonathan Aranda** specifically benefiting from a +12% adjustment for a favorable platoon matchup against Woods Richardson.\n\nThe primary lineup construction decision centered on the bottom of the order, where **Gavin Sheets** (51.27) squeezed into the final UTIL slot. **Jung Hoo Lee** was the most difficult exclusion, finishing at a 50.73; while **Jung Hoo Lee** enjoys a strong platoon advantage against Max Meyer, his lower projected upside in home runs and RBI relative to the rest of the utility pool forced him to the bench. We are also monitoring several \"Lineup Pending\" statuses, specifically for **Will Smith**, **Luis Arraez**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, **Matt Chapman**, **Tyler Freeman**, and **Gavin Sheets**. Any significant shifts in their projected batting order will impact their run-scoring potential. Additionally, users should note that **Taylor Ward** faces a high-risk matchup against Early, whose 2.34 xERA represents the toughest test on our slate; while the park factor keeps **Taylor Ward** viable, the downward pressure from the pitcher\u2019s skill rating remains a primary risk factor. Finally, **Gleyber Torres** was excluded with a score of 38.69, falling well below our 40-point efficiency floor as he continues to struggle with platoon-neutral splits against Lowder.",
